<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 22 at 3:40PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A cluster of strong thunderstorms will impact portions of western
Moore, north central Scotland, southeastern Montgomery, Richmond and
northwestern Hoke Counties through 415 PM EDT...
At 340 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles north of Rockingham, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Southern Pines, Rockingham, Pinehurst, Hamlet, Aberdeen, Hoffman,
Pinebluff, Ellerbe, Foxfire and Candor.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
